Four people were charged with murder and the rest with human trafficking in connection with the death of 71 migrants in August 2015. BUDAPEST- Hungarian prosecutors on Thursday charged 11 people, four of them with murder and all with human trafficking, in connection with the death of 71 migrants found in a lorry by an Austrian motorway in August 2015.A statement from the prosecution office of B cs-Kiskun county, from where the lorry set out on its fatal journey, said it had asked for life sentences for four men and fixed-term prison sentences and expulsion for the rest of the accused.Four men participated in the transport of the 71 migrants directly with the rest involved in sustaining a network that made hundreds of thousands of euros from human smuggling, the statement said, as thousands of refugees and migrants crossed the Balkans that year.